title: Project Atlas — Customer Portal Rebuild
summary: Replace the legacy customer portal with a unified, accessible web app — Phase 1 plan
meta: | type: project-plan | ref: PLAN-2026-031 | sponsor: VP Digital | manager: Lina Haddad | status: in-progress | theme: corporate

toc:

section: 1. Overview
text: Project Atlas rebuilds the Northwind customer portal on a single modern stack, retiring three legacy systems. This document is the Phase 1 plan covering discovery through public beta. It is the source of truth for scope, schedule, ownership, and sign-off; the seal is applied once the steering committee approves the baseline.
text: The plan is reviewed weekly. Tasks, decisions, and milestones below are queryable; reporting is generated directly from this file.

objective: Cut average support-ticket resolution time by 40% | metric: avg-resolution | baseline: 14h | target: 8h
objective: Reach WCAG 2.2 AA conformance across all portal flows | owner: Accessibility Lead
objective: Migrate 100% of active accounts off the legacy portal | count: 84000 | by: 2026-11-30

section: 2. Scope
sub: 2.1 In Scope
- Account dashboard, billing history, and self-service payments
- Support ticket creation and status tracking
- Single sign-on across portal, mobile app, and help center
- Full WCAG 2.2 AA accessibility pass

sub: 2.2 Out of Scope
- Native mobile apps (tracked separately under Project Beacon)
- Back-office agent console (Phase 2)
- Loyalty program integration (Phase 2)

info: Anything not listed as In Scope is Phase 2 by default. Scope changes require a logged decision and re-approval of the baseline. | type: warning

section: 3. Workstreams & Tasks
sub: 3.1 Discovery
done: User research interviews with 18 customers | at: 2026-05-22
done: Legacy portal data audit and field mapping | at: 2026-06-02
task: Finalize information architecture and sitemap | owner: Priya Nair | due: 2026-07-04 | priority: high
task: Accessibility audit of current portal (baseline) | owner: Tom Avery | due: 2026-07-08 | priority: medium

sub: 3.2 Design
task: Component library and design tokens | owner: Priya Nair | due: 2026-07-25 | priority: high
task: High-fidelity prototypes for top 5 flows | owner: Priya Nair | due: 2026-08-08 | priority: high
task: Usability test prototype with 8 users | owner: Tom Avery | due: 2026-08-15 | priority: medium

sub: 3.3 Engineering
done: Provision staging environment and CI pipeline | at: 2026-06-10
task: Authentication and SSO service | owner: Marcus Lee | due: 2026-08-22 | priority: high
task: Account dashboard frontend | owner: Sofia Reyes | due: 2026-09-12 | priority: high
task: Payments integration with billing provider | owner: Marcus Lee | due: 2026-09-26 | priority: high
task: Support ticket module | owner: Sofia Reyes | due: 2026-10-10 | priority: medium

sub: 3.4 Data Migration
task: Build account migration ETL and dry-run | owner: Raj Patel | due: 2026-09-05 | priority: high
task: Production migration rehearsal (staging) | owner: Raj Patel | due: 2026-10-24 | priority: high

dependency: Payments integration | blocked-by: Authentication and SSO service | reason: SSO token required for payment session
dependency: Production migration rehearsal | blocked-by: Build account migration ETL and dry-run | reason: rehearsal runs the validated ETL

risk: Billing provider API rate limits during bulk migration | severity: high | likelihood: medium | mitigation: batch migration off-peak with backoff
risk: SSO rollout breaks existing legacy sessions | severity: medium | likelihood: low | mitigation: dual-token bridge for 30 days
risk: Accessibility rework discovered late in build | severity: medium | likelihood: medium | mitigation: audit baseline before design sign-off

section: 4. Decisions
decision: Adopt React with server components over a full SSR framework | by: Marcus Lee | at: 2026-06-09 | rationale: lower migration risk, team familiarity
decision: Use the existing billing provider rather than re-platforming payments | by: Lina Haddad | at: 2026-06-12 | rationale: keeps Phase 1 on schedule
decision: Public beta is invite-only before general availability | by: VP Digital | at: 2026-06-18 | rationale: contain support load during cutover

